HE reader will remember a picture which caused such a stir in Parisian art cirles. It was a young girl, dark-eyed, black-haired‚ brown-faced‚ lithe, innocent, clothed in white and dull scarlet, sitting on a rustic seat under a huge, moss-hung, live-oak tree. In the back ground there was a glimpse of an old gray mansion with a ‹lecaying veranda and a many-gabled roof.
